<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="8" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,1180,1807]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,303,1181,1207]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Description.</emphasis>
Body length: ɗ 8.0mm. Body colour generally brown to dark brown; anteclypeus and lora dark with pair of stout setae apically on anteclypeus (
<figureCitation box="[737,810,1221,1247]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="22.[151,255,1703,1727]" captionTargetBox="[200,1394,225,1642]" captionTargetId="figure@22.[173,1424,194,1679]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="FIGURE 9. Cyrta coalita sp. n. A, head and thorax, dorsal view; B, face; C, aedeagus, ventral view; D, style and connective, dorsal view; E, style, connective and aedeagus, lateral view; F, male genital capsule, ventral view; G, male genital capsule, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/182585/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
Fig. 
<number box="[794,810,1221,1247]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="9.0">9</number>
</figureCitation>
B). Scutellum with very short tufts of black hairlike setae on lateral margin (
<figureCitation box="[432,502,1261,1287]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="22.[151,255,1703,1727]" captionTargetBox="[200,1394,225,1642]" captionTargetId="figure@22.[173,1424,194,1679]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="FIGURE 9. Cyrta coalita sp. n. A, head and thorax, dorsal view; B, face; C, aedeagus, ventral view; D, style and connective, dorsal view; E, style, connective and aedeagus, lateral view; F, male genital capsule, ventral view; G, male genital capsule, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/182585/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
Fig. 
<number box="[487,502,1261,1287]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="9.0">9</number>
</figureCitation>
A).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,1180,1807]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
Male pygofer with short to long macrosetae and very dense short setae; with a long dorsally curved inner process and process with two denticles on dorsal margin at about one third part (
<figureCitation box="[1088,1157,1341,1367]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="22.[151,255,1703,1727]" captionTargetBox="[200,1394,225,1642]" captionTargetId="figure@22.[173,1424,194,1679]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="FIGURE 9. Cyrta coalita sp. n. A, head and thorax, dorsal view; B, face; C, aedeagus, ventral view; D, style and connective, dorsal view; E, style, connective and aedeagus, lateral view; F, male genital capsule, ventral view; G, male genital capsule, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/182585/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
Fig. 
<number box="[1142,1157,1341,1367]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="9.0">9</number>
</figureCitation>
G). Subgenital plate not extending beyond to apex of pygofer side; fused with valve basally (
<figureCitation box="[976,1049,1381,1407]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="22.[151,255,1703,1727]" captionTargetBox="[200,1394,225,1642]" captionTargetId="figure@22.[173,1424,194,1679]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="FIGURE 9. Cyrta coalita sp. n. A, head and thorax, dorsal view; B, face; C, aedeagus, ventral view; D, style and connective, dorsal view; E, style, connective and aedeagus, lateral view; F, male genital capsule, ventral view; G, male genital capsule, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/182585/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
Fig. 
<number box="[1033,1049,1381,1407]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="9.0">9</number>
</figureCitation>
F). Aedeagal shaft broad basally and tapered to apex in both lateral and ventral view, apex acute in lateral view and narrowly rounded in ventral view (
<figureCitation box="[223,297,1461,1487]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="22.[151,255,1703,1727]" captionTargetBox="[200,1394,225,1642]" captionTargetId="figure@22.[173,1424,194,1679]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="FIGURE 9. Cyrta coalita sp. n. A, head and thorax, dorsal view; B, face; C, aedeagus, ventral view; D, style and connective, dorsal view; E, style, connective and aedeagus, lateral view; F, male genital capsule, ventral view; G, male genital capsule, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/182585/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
Figs 
<number box="[282,297,1461,1487]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="9.0">9</number>
</figureCitation>
C, E).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
