<subSubSection box="[197,1253,1581,1607]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,1180,1807]" box="[197,1253,1581,1607]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,338,1581,1607]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific name is derived from its subgenital plates fused to valve basally.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="8" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,1180,1807]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,318,1621,1647]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species is similar to 
<taxonomicName box="[628,762,1621,1646]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Cyrta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="striolata">
<emphasis box="[628,762,1621,1646]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">C. striolata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[778,934,1621,1646]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Cyrta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flosifronta">
<emphasis box="[778,934,1621,1646]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">C. flosifronta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[949,1096,1621,1646]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Cyrta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="incurvata">
<emphasis box="[949,1096,1621,1646]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">C. incurvata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[1155,1317,1621,1646]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Cyrta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fujianensis">
<emphasis box="[1155,1317,1621,1646]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">C. fujianensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having an inner pygofer process. It can be distinguished from these by: 
<number box="[901,914,1661,1687]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="1.0">1</number>
) subgenital plate acute apically and fused to valve basally; 
<number box="[327,342,1701,1727]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="2.0">2</number>
) inner process of pygofer with two denticles on dorsal margin at about one third part; 
<number box="[1412,1427,1701,1727]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="3.0">3</number>
) aedeagal shaft broad basally and tapered to apex in both lateral and ventral view, apex acute in lateral view and narrowly rounded in ventral view.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
